Looking at this position, I can see that the White king on f2 is in a very exposed position, and my queen on c1 is ideally placed to deliver a decisive blow.

I notice that if I play Qg1, it would deliver checkmate because:
- The queen would attack the king on f2
- All escape squares (e1, e2, e3, f1, g2, g3) would be controlled by the queen
- f3 is occupied by White's own bishop

This is a forced checkmate in one move.
